<node id="f09ece78e015">
  <data key="d0">paragraph</data>
  <data key="d1">Observation</data>
  <data key="d2">0</data>
  <data key="d3">KV eviction and compression methods reduce long-context inference cost by limiting the size or precision of KV caches during decoding. Eviction-based approaches such as H2O ( Zhang et al. , 2023 ) and StreamingLLM ( Xiao et al. , 2023 ) discard cached KV states based on heuristics, includ- ing recency or attention importance. Compression methods such as Pyramid KV ( Cai et al. , 2024 ) and memoriz</data>
  <data key="d4">0.8</data>
  <data key="d5">0.2511</data>
  <data key="d6">550.4385375976562</data>
  <data key="d7">aaee53921e65</data>
  <data key="d8">False</data>
</node>
