  <data key="d1">Method</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
  <data key="d3">where d h is the per-head dimension. In practice, inference consists of a prefilling phase that computes KV states for an input context of length L in a single forward pass, followed by an iterative decoding phase that appends one new KV pair per generated token. In long-context question answering, where the generated answer is short, inference cost is often dominated by the prefilling stage.</data>
