  <data key="d1">Definition</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
  <data key="d3">Let the input consist of N tokens, which we partition into K disjoint chunks { C 1 , . . . , C K } . Each chunk serves as a basic unit for prefilling and can correspond to a naturally independent segment (e.g., a document or an image), or a contiguous partition of a single long input (e.g., a text sequence or a visual token grid).</data>
  <data key="d4">0.8</data>
